I conducted forensic work with teenagers and their families, as well as with adults and couples. And at this point in my career, I'm working almost exclusively with individuals who are over the age of 18 in both my forensic and clinical practices. Q. In addition to running a group practice, do you work anywhere else? A. I do. Q. Where do you work? A. I'm on the faculty, the clinical faculty at Brown University School of Medicine. Q. Do you work in a particular department within Brown University School of Medicine? A. Within the department of psychiatry. Q. What is your title? A. Clinical assistant professor. Q. How long have you taught at Brown University's medical school? A. Since June of 2020. Q. And what are your current responsibilities in your job at Brown? A. I supervise psychiatrists in training, so psychiatric fellows who are learning how to do adult psychotherapy. I also conduct seminars around issues pertaining to trauma and traumatic stress. SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300 DOJ-OGR-00012317
